metadata.name: Yellow River into the Sea (黄河入海流)
metadata.description:
"Climbing the Stork Tower" by Wang Zhihuan

Standing on the tall building, I saw the sunset slowly sinking against the mountains, and the surging Yellow River rushing towards the sea.  
If you want to see the scenery thousands of miles away, you have to go up a higher floor.

唐代王之涣的《登鹳雀楼》

白日依山尽，黄河入海流。  
欲穷千里目，更上一层楼。
